The paper discusses the design and performance evaluation of automatic traffic report generation systems, which involves handling huge data volumes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to data management, artificial intelligence, machine learning, information retrieval, and cryptography. Specifically, cs.DB (databases), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.LG (machine learning) are likely because they deal with handling and analyzing large amounts of data. cs.IR (information retrieval) is also possible because the paper discusses the generation of reports from traffic data. Finally, cs.CR (cryptography) is a less likely possibility, but it cannot be completely ruled out since the paper may discuss security and privacy issues related to traffic data.
